< text>
H Cabinet is a warehouse, no frills. Everything is on display. They have cabinets, cabinet knobs, flooring, kitchen countertops of various materials, and stainless steel sinks. You browse and select then a rep will help you. If you bring your measurements they will put your cabinet selections in a CAD presentation. They will load your truck and you're done. They also offer cabinet assembly.
The parking lot is small, but it turns over quickly.<//text>

<Gmap_id>0x80dd2d3de7ef31ed:0x2c5191a04de346b9<//Gmap_id>< Time>
1470671809677<//Time>
<review>BETWEEN THE REVIEWS w/ Rodney S

Q)  What brought you to Douglas Burgers, Rodney?
A)  Valpak, Rodney.  Valpak had a coupon for a BOGO 1/4 lb hamburger Mon - Thurs.  Seeing a good deal when I see one, I had to seize the opportunity.

Q)  How was Douglas' 1/4 lb hamburger?
A)  At only $2.99, the BOGO hamburgers were a definite bargain.  However, the patty was thin.  I'm talking almost "White Castle thin".  It does make for faster cooking time, but the thinness also made for a well done burger.  I would've much preferred a juicier patty with a little pink.  The usual tomatoes, onions, pickles & thousand island were present.  I always get my burgers lettuce-wrapped, and Douglas accommodated my request.

Q)  Rodney, what else does Douglas Burgers have to offer?
A)  An extensive menu, consisting of burgers, sandwiches, breakfast items, Mexican food etc. keeps diners guessing as to what to get.  Specials include a burger, fries & drink for $4.99.

Q)  Another other info you can share?
A)  Yes, Rodney.  Service was okay.  My order was taken quickly and I didn't wait too long before I was chowing down on my BOGO burgers.  Plenty of booth seating, with flatscreens to watch the latest soccer games.  Parking is in a private lot, with street parking available, too.  Douglas Burgers is located in a shady area. How shady, Rodney?  Well, the liquor store next to the restaurant has bulletproof plastic protecting the cashier.  Yeah, that shady.

Q)  Would you recommend eating at Douglas Burgers?
A)  Being that the burger patty was uber thin & the aforementioned neighborhood being not too family friendly, I don't recommend eating at Douglas Burgers.  There are plenty of similar options in and around my local area, that have juicier burgers and where I don't have to worry about someone busting a cap nearby & ruining my meal.<//review><name>Rodney S</name><Pictures>None</Pictures>< response>
None</response>

< Review>
Good taste, small wings.
Not your grandad Granites.
This place used to have big wings big sandwiches, friendly staff.
The NAME is granites but wow it sucks compared to the old owners.
Little wings with paltry meat. Not as many choices of heat. And the man and woman behind the counter were NOT friendly at all!
Plus $.85 per wing for such anorexic wings is a RIP off.

I was sad when I opened the box of wings at home and saw how small the wings were.
And no bucket of pickles like they used to have.

The best summary words will have to be "let down". The inferno was pretty decent taste wise.
I will not be returning.<//Review>

First time here, SO GOOD. First of all, the crab is huge and packed with meat. The soup is super refreshing, you can also choose the level of spiciness to your liking. I personally think this place tastes better than a lot of the places in Korea that sell the same menus. I can't wait to come try all the other menus in the near future. Highly recommended.
P.S. The staff were super sweet and accommodated our needs very well.</review>

We had to flag down our server multiple times to recieve service and when we finally got the bill i left a tip that fitted the service we received. The server ran out as we were waiting for our vehicle and said that we had added our tip wrong. Not having my glasses i went ahead and fixed the amount, only to find out from my daughter that the amount i had originally put was correct. She basically scammed me out of 13 more dollars to add to her tip. I called and reported what had happened and now she will recieve no tip. It is the proprietary of the situation , she should not have lied to me and on my fault i should have got my glasses out and doubled checked but we had engagement to run too . I already called my bank to let them know that if they run a larger amount to dispute it, i will pay for what i ate but now NO TIP will be added. I advice that if you are visiting or live here do not come here, they are cheats and want more money  for crap service, I do not advice this place at all.</Text>

< review>
Do yourself a favor and shop somewhere else. IKEA, Target, Bed Bath & Beyond, or anywhere else but here. Everything, every single item is just way too overpriced. A salt/pepper grinder? $49.99! ONE clear plastic cup made out of the cheapest plastic? $3.99! Whoever priced the merchandise smoked the cheapest stuff on the market and just slapped the price tags randomly on everything. It's a nice store, very nice indeed. But there is no point of wasting 3-4 times the money on stuff you can buy somewhere else!< /review>

< review>
Simple as possible, my daughters XV party;
* Host Sarine, attentive and great communicator. A+
* Location: Safe and a local attraction area with great view and very clean. A+
* Food: Full course meal. Appetizers, Main dishes. A+
* Service: Great attention to guests, food was coming out non stop.A+
* Space: Ginormous. A+
* Full Service Bar: Lives up to the title, Full Service. A+
* Parking: This is the only downside, no free parking unless you find a free space 2+ blocks away, which isn't that bad considering the venue and area. Worth it. You can also pay for parking across the street for $9.00 all night.

We plan on our next even at one of their other locations soon since we loved the experience here!

Thank you Sarine and team!

Fred< /review>

Not only was everything perfect, it was beyond anything we could have imagined.

< Review>
L.A. Banquet - Brandview Ballroom ‚Äì Celestina & William Wedding Sept. 5th, 2014.

Before I get into the reviews I want to give a Gigantic THANK YOU!!!!, to the LA Banquets and Anoush Catering staff.¬† My wife and I cannot stop talking about this unforgettable day not because the venue was awesome but because of the Anoush Catering staff. ¬† Adam, Greg, Norik, Christian and Vrej fully comprehend that at the core of rendering service are people and relationships. They were welcoming and open to making our dream wedding come to pass and worked with us throughout the entire process. Their genuine interest and care showed at the wedding, we had no complaints from our guests.

We selected the Brandview Ballroom on Valentine‚Äôs Day 2014. We were looking for a venue that ¬†had character, great locations, easy parking, great hotels, lots of wedding experience and able to handle 250+ guests. By the way our guest list ended up growing to 430 and this was no sweat for Norik or Greg.¬† What was important to us was that our guests had more than enough food, were well treated and celebrated our marriage in an awesome atmosphere. ¬†Brandview Ballroom and Anoush Catering hit it out the park!!!!

The venue was clean and had a royal feel to it with the spiral staircase and chandelier.¬† There was plenty of parking and the valet parking service is next to the entrance.¬† They provided great valet service, all valet attendants had clean uniforms and polished shoes.¬† This space had a renovated patio and was more than big enough to accommodate guest sign in.¬† The lighting was great, the space allowed the music to be heard and also the guests did not have to yell to be heard.

My wife and I do not drink but we heard nothing but great things from those who were at the bar.¬† They made our choice drinks and we wished they had brought it to our tables because the one we tasted was just just perfect.

Anoush Catering also worked and accommodated all of our vendors and treated them with respect and consistently offered their support to our vendors to make their work easy.¬† They made sure the venue was open with enough time for the DJ, the florist, the bakery to deliver their service with excellence.¬† When we walked into the venue everything we discussed and wanted was there.¬† I am anal at times and even with everything going on I went through my check list and nothing was missing.

They even allowed us to keep stuff there until the next day because we had so many gifts.¬† They allowed us to take all of the food that was left over.

Above all things my wife was very happy with her wedding and she did not want the night to end.¬† We were the last ones to leave and we savor all the great moments and awesome time.¬† Happy wife makes a happy husband.

Although the lighting was great we wanted all the lights dim except for the dance floor light when we were having our speeches and that did not happen but it was okay.

Much appreciation and thanks to L.A. Banquet and Anoush Catering.¬† Five star all the way around.!!!!!!</Review>

We've been going to Salitos every time we have any occasion (birthday, anniversary and so on). But our last time yesterday was terrible. Our reservation was for 6.15pm, but had to wait for 30 more minutes to get seated. We ordered crab pasta, home salad with shrimps and cioppino. Everything was mediocre except for pasta- we liked it. Right away when we finished our dinner, I felt terrible and sick. By now I've been laying down for a second day because of food poisoning. I think the problem was with raw shrimps that were in our salad (although we hadn't been told that  the "add shrimps" to the salad option means the shrimps will be raw as we usually try to avoid unprocessed food). It was definitely our last time that we went to Salitos!</Text>

Salito's Crab House is fantastic! We stopped in for lunch while in Sausalito and sat near the open back room with a great view of the boats! The fish sandwich and the fish & chips are massive and take up the whole plate. The portions are huge, and the wait staff is very friendly, quick, and do a great job of checking on you throughout your meal. The area is super busy and parking is a bit sparse. They have their own parking lot but it fills up quickly, your best bet is to find paid street parking. Next time I'm in town, I'm going to stop in again.< /text>

< text>
On a weekend get-away, compared to the extremely over-crowded places nearby (2hr+ waits), this place had great service and seats with a great view within 5-10 minutes.

The crab is incredibly tasty with a (admittedly strong) buttery garlic sauce that goes well with bread (99c for some hot fresh bread to go with). We also had some cheap wine to go with, reasonably fast service. We spent around 2 hours just enjoying our meal and drinks with the view here, relaxed atmosphere.

I think if we'd ordered some of the single-person meals the quality of the food may not have been as good, this definitely is a seafood-first sort of place, the mussels and crabs are what they specialize in, so I can see why the other food may not be as tasty.<//text>

Crab bisque in a bread bowl is huge, perfect for a chilly day looking over the bay, and the bread is the highlight of an already fantastic bowl of bisque. Mussels are amazing here - fresh, perfectly cooked, great flavors. The mussel sizes truly are for sharing, so watch out and order smaller. Seafood linguine was the standout of the meal though. The ratio of seafood to linguine was outrageous. Piles of perfectly cooked seafood hid the bits of slightly aldente linguine, with a sauce that tied the whole plate together. I am a seafoodaholic and I needed a break from seafood after this meal. It was damn near perfect, and so much of it. On a side note, the desserts were nothing to slouch at either. They are all excellent, so whatever floats your boat. And, of course, it's hard to beat the atmosphere - Sausalito, in the water, outside. What more could you want?< /Text><rate>5< /rate>< Gmap_id>

<user>114801832272278834842<//user>< text>
Nice place to take a company or date. Or just plain treatin' yoself. This place probably has the fanciest and greater fish n chips I've ever had. I was expecting some fried fish with a golden color without any seasoning, but this one definitely surprised me.

However, the sandwiches are definitely not their specialty. My friends who had them were okay with it, but wasn't fully satisfied. The calamari were delicious as well as their oysters.

I'd go here again if I'm in the area or want to take someone out. Great views and service.<//text>

< Review>
I came here for dinner the other night with my man and all I have to say is WOWWWW. Everything about the food and experience was just out of this world. We made reservations, got there early and ordered cocktails while we waited which I loved (plus the cocktails were strong and BOMB). At the table we ordered the cast iron bread and brussel sprouts to start--  the bread and butter was so real and fresh like they made it to order! And the brussel sprouts were crispy and so well-seasoned. The seating layout outside was nice and the sunset was so dreamy!! We ordered pasta and steak, and got a good suggestion for wine and every single bite was just PERFECT. And everything was well-priced. Our server [Megan] just took the experience over the top with her positive attitude and expertise on the restaurant and city. And she treated surrounding tables with the same care so you know it's real. Lol I was so sad to leave and cannot WAIT to come back and get a table right at the rails. This is seriously my new favorite place with the best memories. üòä

I'd say the only thing that made this restaurant feel less than of its caliber is the fact that the host was wearing a shirt that was a little short or not fitted well, so you could see her stomach and love handles-- which significantly decreases professionalism anywhere.< /Review>

< Review>
My personal dish was not my favorite, but the service was great and the food was overall fun and inventive! We got the crabwich, crab alfredo, and two orders of crab enchiladas. If you like Cioppino you will like the enchiladas. The sandwich was light and yummy (not full of mayo like most crab sandwiches) and the Alfredo was very delicious. We also got a liter draft beer (only 9.99) so we had a great time. The back area is amazing on a sunny day because it is open to  the waterfront view, try to get a seat there!</Review>

< name>
Anna Leigh Peek< /name>
<time>1536176455716< /time><rating>3<//rating>< Text>
Made a reservation through OpenTable. Arrived 15 minutes prior to reservation to be told there would be a wait. We waited an hour past our reservation time and were finally seated. The poor young girl that was the hostess didn't seem to be a seasoned hostess. She had a list of reservations, our name was not put on that list she kept showing I'm assuming the manager, ours name was written in crayon on a different list. Anyways, we were still better off than some people that came in with/before us. When we were seated, our waitress was very nice, said she would be right with us, but that it would probably be 5-10 minutes, fine, at least she warned us. It was her second day on the job and it was a busy night, I think she did well considering. She was very kind and did her best. We ordered an appetizer and our food at the same time and they were both out at almost the same time and within 10 minutes. Once we actually got to the food it was great. The kettle bread and cheese was phenomenal, I think it would have been just as good without the cheese. I could have took bread home for later it was that good. I had the spicy shrimp pasta, it was delicious and while it didn't look like a big portion for the price, it was filling. My friend had the roasted shrimp, she said it was good, just a little cumbersome to have to peel it all before eating it. Food was five star, service has some work to do (mostly on on the seating portion). The food was some of the best on our trip, I would return, just maybe later in the evening (after 8:30) or earlier in the evening (4:30 or 5).<//Text>

<user_id>116606509585874095184<//user_id><name>Art Thompson<//name><Time>1570330312643</Time><rate>4< /rate>< review>
I had an excellent evening at Solito's yesterday. The vibe, venue, waterfront views, staff friendliness, and food were great. Barry White was even laying out his soul music in the background. It's definitely a comfortable scene. I highly recommend the brussel sprouts and kettle bread. My crabcakes were alright, and could have benefited by that special crab cake foodie touch of the eastern shore of Maryland or Delaware. While eating, I couldn't stop thinking of the crab cakes at Matt's Fish Camp, Lewes, DE of a few weeks ago. A wider selection of craft beers on tap would be nice, too. Overall, a solid positive experience, and I'll be back.</review>

< Text>
I had an excellent evening at Solito's yesterday. The vibe, venue, waterfront views, staff friendliness, and food were great. Barry White was even laying out his soul music in the background. It's definitely a comfortable scene. I highly recommend the brussel sprouts and kettle bread. My crabcakes were alright, and could have benefited by that special crab cake foodie touch of the eastern shore of Maryland or Delaware. While eating, I couldn't stop thinking of the crab cakes at Matt's Fish Camp, Lewes, DE of a few weeks ago. A wider selection of craft beers on tap would be nice, too. Overall, a solid positive experience, and I'll be back.</Text>

<UserId.>104364765326270687703</UserId.>< user_name>
Corey Masters<//user_name>
<time>1546411624772</time><rate>5<//rate>< Review>
The bay area is famous for its fine seafood, but Salito's really distinguishes itself from the rest. Seafood itself is predictable fare; nothing wrong with comfort food. Salito's conforms to these expectations in its dishes, but does something special to elevate each dish. My Dungeness crab was poached so excellently in garlic butter, it was almost funny that melted butter was included. It certainly wasn't needed. The service at Salito's is interesting; they are very popular and busy so they have adapted the service to accommodate. The service experience is a little impersonal, seeing a multitude of faces, but operates like a well-oiled machine. I got my food so quickly I was tempted to just order more.<//Review>

<Date>1487131755246< /Date>< Review>
Only been here once, but everything was excellent. We were seated and served promptly. We loved the open air atmosphere, as the restaurant opens to the water but yet customers are covered overhead and kept warm with outdoor heaters.

I had the garlic noodles with crab, which was excellent. Noodles cooked perfectly, still a bit firm, with a good portion of crab. My wife had salad and crab chowder in a bread bowl and loved it. Make sure to get the kettle bread - incredible!

Parking is tough, so if you dine during busy hours expect to park 100 yards away.<//Review>

We returned and brought some guests here for a Monday lunch. The crab and super combo was better than I remember, but the steak is simply disappointing, I can't believe they call this ham-looking thing a prime steak. Brought out onto the table half cold.

< Text>
2 stars for location, 1 star for food and service.  Locals visiting for a birthday celebration.  This is a churn and burn type of establishment.  Drinks were good.  Generous pours.  The appetizers were good fair price for the quality and portions of food being served.  Lunch deteriorated from there.  Entrees came before our salads.  Our waiter, while apologetic, struggled to recover but it just wasn't possible. There wasn't enough room on the table for our entrees and salads.

I ordered crab and prime rib.  Crab was clearly overcooked and held.  It was extremely dry and hard to remove from the shell.  The prime rib was cooked as ordered, but my 16oz of meat was ice cold when served. Again, not something the server could recover from.  Wine was decent, but costly for vintage and age.  My wife had crab enchiladas, came home and promptly threw up.   She doesn't have a weak stomach.  Some how I managed to avoid whatever she must have eaten.

Charging a premium and being premium are very different things.  Expect to be gouged if you eat here.  I'd rate this location as a cocktail only establishment.  You can get better food and service,  at a lower price close by.

Guys you need to step up your game.  The entire staff, from the kitchen down needs to be retrained.  There was zero coordination between the kitchen, bussers and servers.  They were all over each other and neither knew what the other was doing.  I know you can do better than this. Would I come back to eat here, no way.< /Text>

<Review>My boyfriend and I came here because of the reviews. We love prime rib, and crab and we wanted a good meal to celebrate our anniversary.

1) we sat right away
2) our table and seats were still dirty with crumbs
3) we ordered the crab fondue as an appetizer
a) it was watery
b) lukewarm
c) minimal crab
d) the toast was cold and stale unedible
e) the plates the gave us were dirty
4) we ordered wine
a) our wine glasses placed on the table upon ordering were dirty
5) we both ordered prime rib
a) very fatty pieces of meat lukewarm as well
b) the "vegetables" : Carrots, Black olives, shallots, corn
1) all cold and "old tatsing"
c) the potatoes : deep fried and smashed

We couldn't send our appetizer back until our server came with the bill, because that was the first and last time he checked on us. When we expresses our concerns about the entire meal he gave us the impression he wanted us quickly out just for the quick turnaround.

Our bill was over a hundred dollars, and we were no where near satisfied or happy. We got nothing we paid for.

I called and spoke with the manager and he gave a pretty generic response, he took my number and never heard back from him. They, in my opinion do not care about the service they provide, and the quality of the entire experience, ans it should be wondered what happens behind the scenes with what we saw on the stage.

We will not be returning, nor ever recommending this restaurant to anyone in this area. <review>If you come to Salito's Crab House you gotta sit on the patio, just right on the water. The view is absolutely beautiful on a sunny day.

First of all even though I am a fan of the restaurant they gotta do something about their staff I have been there twice last year and it's the same issues. They seem a little nonchalant and slow! very very slow! We asked about 3 different people for water and finally got it after a 15minute wait. I mean it's just water!

Anyway, bad service aside, the food a really good! The fish and chips is a must have! It's technically not chips, it's a kind of baked/fried potato, just great trust me!

I also had their Basa Inferno, it comes in a skillet and it's quite good. It's couscous, fish tomato sauce and some Habanero peppers.

It's definite worth to try but I hope they improve their service a little more to make the experience perfect.<//review>< rate>

<Time>1622833332254<//Time>< GmapID>
0x808584516e36f9b9:0xd062e5c18afb1242<//GmapID>
< Text>
Please bring back the surf and turf special from pre-covid!
The crab here is SO good. They season it really well. Green onions, garlic and butter, I think. I could eat loads more of it. The corn, sweet potatoes, smashed whole potatoes, olives, are very tasty too. Also seasoned well - they use some seaweed, sesame seed salt. Best crab I've had.
The prime rib is tasty and comes with the same sides.
House salad is a step above regular house salads and very pretty. Has avocado, radish. Needs some lemon.
The beignets were delicious. Needed a bit more powdered sugar.
Panna cotta, also tasty, was light and delicate.
Beautiful views on their balcony. And the heat lamps were more than toasty. Service can be a little slower, but gives you time to enjoy the view and tasty food.

Crab and sides better than The Old Clam House on Bayshore Blvd in SF. Also safer area, better parking, views and food in general.

Highly recommend. Definitely coming back.</Text>

< text>
I wish I could give Salito's half a star or less...

If you are looking for a great dinning experience in this area, there are many other options. I would highly recommend Sushi Ran!!!! Scoma's, The Trident, or The Spinnaker would too make for better options. Please heed this warning!

My girlfriend and I made dinner reservations three weeks prior to our trip and the reservations were ignored. When we walked into the restaurant, the hostess haphazardly handed us menus and said it was open seating. We awkwardly waited five minutes for the booth we originally requested in our reservation. Our server, Neve, did not come to our table for another 15 minutes. When he finally showed up to our table, he asked us what we wanted to eat in an unwelcoming manner. He not only neglected to introduce himself, but he also didn't give us a run-through of the menu or the daily specials. We ordered some over-priced crab cakes and one drink. After an hour of sitting and waiting, we asked to leave. Managers and corporate representatives were contacted many times, but nobody cared to take responsibility. We not only drove 1,201+ miles for this vacation, but also live and work in Colorado and the best this company claims they can do is to offer us a dining voucher for the value we spent on August the 14th. My girlfriend works in the dining industry and we are both dumbfounded. Notice also that this post is going up on September 7th; this is how long we have been dealing with this headache. Simply put: seek out other dining options!!!!< /text>

My husband LOVED his spicy pasta. My fish - meh. It was really very bland and tasteless. The location is AMAZING, and the ginger martini was lovely. There were open tables right on the water when we got there, and when asked if we could sit there, we were told, "No, we save those for larger parties". Ok, fine, like I mentioned, the views were still amazing - except that two other couples were seated on the water about 15 minutes later. Maybe it was because it was a Wednesday night, but other than the views and the martini, this place was very blah.< /review>

< Review>
Great service. Really great food. The chorizo cheese bread is outstanding. The crab chowder is really good. Crab enchiladas are amazing. And their fish and chips!? Those are the best fish and chips I have ever had. Basically a whole lightly fried fillet but absolutely perfectly cooked and flakey every time. Overall a great spot. Nice that it isn't as packed nor is it as expensive as some places in sausalito. Also really good views.</Review>

Terrible food and service.  The spinach cheese dip was lukewarm and gooey/solid.  The prime rib was unremarkable as was the 1/2 dungeness crab that I ordered with it.  I asked for drawn butter for the crab and was given a partially melted tub of butter.  The only thing I got that was any good was the beet salad.  The fish fry was ok.  I brought my sister and brother in law here and was embarrassed at the food quality.  It does have a nice setting on the water.</Review>

Came in after fishing in the AM looking to have a nice cold beer at an outdoor bar in Sausalito.  We happened upon Salito's, went to the back porch bar, and the bar tender refused to serve us, accusing us of being on drugs, and being drunk (admittedly we had just finished fishing so we looked scrubby). We then approached the manager, Jorge, informed him of what happened, and he refused to acknowledge the experience. My conclusion is as follows: Restaurant NPS score = 0. NEVER recommending to anyone. ANYONE. We then went to Bar Bocce & Joinery, and had a fantastic time, dining experience and customer experience. Would highly recommend Bar Bocce or Joinery to anyone!!!< /Review>

<name>Russ Laraway</name>< Time>
1503275469548<//Time>
<Rating>2<//Rating>< Review>
Not good value, too pricey for mediocre quality

Good
- setting, decor, view
- menu

Bad
- service was atrocious (a story below)
- fountain soda watered down and not very bubbly
- food was meh

Bad service stories

Story 1
They have crab chowder available in a cup and in a bread bowl for 4 or 5 dollars more than the cup.

I wanted more chowder but not the bread so I asked for a bowl of soup, no bread. They brought out a slightly larger cup of soup.   I looked around at others at my table (party of 10) who had ordered the cup of soup and I noticed I had about the same amount as they did.

I asked the waiter, "This looks like the same amount of soup... do you think this is $4 or $5 more soup than the cup?"

Waiter says he'll look into it.  Now there is only one right answer, which is so simple: tell me you'll charge me for a cup, not a bowl.

Nope.

Waiter comes out with a normal cup filled with water and pours it into the larger cup (my non-bread "bowl"), and I think he's here to show me the great news, that I was right and he was going to charge me for the cup.

Nope.  It becomes almost clear that the bowl volume is ever so slightly larger than the cup volume, and the waiter does a proverbial mic drop "see, sir, there is more soup in the bowl."  Yes, there was at least 2 or 3 tablespoons full.

Even better (story 2), my sister and her family were here... my sister has a gluten allergy, makes that known. After she starts eating waiter comes flying out like he's seen a ghost to inform my sister that the dish she has contains gluten.

She's fine, but this is so bush league...<//Review>

Arrived here lateish on a Friday night with some friends. Place looked like it was going to be a little stodgy from the outside, but when we went in, we were pleasantly surprised. It's open and spacious, and we sat at an outside table right on the water. Lovely.

Had a beef sandwich with dipping jus - really good, and served on their home-made bread. Also recommend their hot beignets for dessert.< /Review>

<Name>–ö—É–º–∫–≤–∞—Ç –ë–∞–≥–æ–µ–≤</Name><time>1579634042654< /time><Rating>5< /Rating><text>(Translated by Google) Great place for a positive gastronomic tourism. At the entrance we were greeted by a rusty anchor and a small queue (in the afternoon!). Our companion exchanged a few words with the hostesses and after a minute we were already very comfortable sitting and enjoying an extremely pleasant atmosphere. It was felt that the guests are carefree and enjoy.
The service is accurate / timely and simple, as if visiting a friend. You realize the importance of the profession of a waiter as an assistant, an intermediary between the kitchen and the guests. The kitchen has left the warmest memories in the hearts of our company.
The restaurant offered us four types of oysters and three sauces for them. I was very surprised at the opportunity to season oysters with special horseradish sauce, however, it was so unobtrusive and unexpectedly elegant for its breed that it did not cause any rejection. Shellfish were excellent! Sea, ocean, freshness and delight! The airy seafood salad (with crab, of course) and the delicate crabcakes that I tried for the first time were very skillfully performed, although they looked quite ordinary. Striploin and filet mignon in combination with baked vegetables (potatoes, sweet potatoes, corn) caused absolute satisfaction with the day, trip and life. To spoil this happiness could only non-starchy cold vegetables in the same plate, which, oh joy, was not in it. And of course, we could not but aggravate all this with the crab, and followed him. Dungeoness is much smaller than Kamchatka, there is not much meat in it, but you have to tinker. It‚Äôs better not to go to him without an apron. He visited our table in a pan, doused with spicy oil, seasoned with "secret garlic sauce." This was hard. We could not. But ate ... two.
For those who think that there is nothing special in the preparation of crab, I recommend to bite freshly cooked crab in a good specialized institution, and then purchase it on the market (for example, in Vladivostok), cooked ashore in the morning. It can be overcooked, overcooked and, oh horror (!!!), overcooked. Crab is easy to make, and spoiling is even easier. At Salito's he was introduced in the best possible way and taste. This unbelievably festive dinner was so inspired that after everything we had eaten, we didn‚Äôt want to give up donuts (fresh hot beignets). So, being overseas, dipping crumpet in cream, I mentally transferred to the small kitchen of my childhood, where my mother fried brushwood in boiling oil.
If you find yourself in the cold San Francisco, you can hardly avoid visiting the famous Golden Gate. Take a ride on the bridge to the other side, visit the warm town of Sausalito. You will have a wonderful view of the bay and the coast with live examples of good cuisine.
